SIMPLE: crampoons
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crampoons
<hw>Cram*poons"</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧m*p⟦oomac⟧nz")</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>crampon</ets>, fr. OHG. <ets>chramph</ets> crooked; akin
to G. <ets>krampf</ets> cramp. See <er>Cramp</er>,<pos>n.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Crampon</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A clutch formed of hooked
pieces of iron, like double calipers, for raising stones, lumber, blocks
of ice, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Iron instruments with sharp points, worn on the
shoes to assist in gaining or keeping a foothold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crampy</ent>⟦br⟧
